WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:14.057 --> 00:01:17.356
Charles. you have
finally lost your senses.

3
00:01:17.393 --> 00:01:19.224
This venture is impossible.

4
00:01:19.262 --> 00:01:22.425
For some. Gentlemen. the only way
to achieve the impossible

5
00:01:22.498 --> 00:01:24.398
is to believe it is possible.

6
00:01:24.434 --> 00:01:26.265
That kind of thinking could ruin you.

7
00:01:26.402 --> 00:01:28.427
I'm willing to take that chance.

8
00:01:28.504 --> 00:01:33.032
Imagine trading posts
in Rangoon. Bangkok. Jakarta...

9
00:01:38.548 --> 00:01:40.413
The nightmare again?

10
00:01:45.421 --> 00:01:47.116
I won't be long.

11
00:01:48.458 --> 00:01:52.121
I'm falling down a dark hole.

12
00:01:53.429 --> 00:01:56.626
then I see strange creatures.

13
00:01:56.933 --> 00:01:59.128
What kind of creatures?

14
00:01:59.202 --> 00:02:05.766
Well. there's a dodo bird.
a rabbit in a waistcoat. a smiling cat.

15
00:02:05.842 --> 00:02:07.935
I didn't know cats could smile.

16
00:02:08.244 --> 00:02:10.235
Neither did I.

17
00:02:10.713 --> 00:02:13.546
And there's a blue caterpillar.

18
00:02:14.584 --> 00:02:16.279
Blue caterpillar.

19
00:02:16.919 --> 00:02:18.079
Hmm.

20
00:02:19.188 --> 00:02:21.850
Do you think I've gone round the bend?

21
00:02:26.462 --> 00:02:31.957
I'm afraid so.
You're mad. bonkers. off your head.

22
00:02:32.835 --> 00:02:36.999
But I'll tell you a secret.
All the best people are.

23
00:02:38.174 --> 00:02:41.666
It's only a dream. Alice.
Nothing can harm you there.

24
00:02:41.744 --> 00:02:45.646
But if you get too frightened.
you can always wake up. Like this.

25
00:02:45.715 --> 00:02:46.977
Ow!

26
00:03:06.369 --> 00:03:07.859
Must we go?

27
00:03:09.305 --> 00:03:11.899
Doubt they'll notice if we never arrive.

28
00:03:11.974 --> 00:03:13.669
They will notice.

29
00:03:16.279 --> 00:03:18.144
Where's your corset?

30
00:03:23.753 --> 00:03:25.345
And no stockings.

31
00:03:25.421 --> 00:03:26.718
I'm against them.

32
00:03:26.789 --> 00:03:28.484
But you're not properly dressed.

33
00:03:28.524 --> 00:03:31.049
Who's to say what is proper?

34
00:03:31.127 --> 00:03:34.392
What if it was agreed that "proper"
was wearing a codfish on your head?

35
00:03:34.463 --> 00:03:36.556
- Would you wear it?
- Alice.

36
00:03:36.632 --> 00:03:39.362
To me. a corset is like a codfish.

37
00:03:39.402 --> 00:03:41.734
Please. not today.

38
00:03:41.804 --> 00:03:43.829
Father would have laughed.

39
00:03:45.408 --> 00:03:50.869
I'm sorry. I'm tired.
I didn't sleep well last night.

40
00:03:51.380 --> 00:03:53.405
Did you have bad dreams again?

41
00:03:53.482 --> 00:03:54.881
Only one.

42
00:03:55.985 --> 00:03:59.045
It's always the same.
ever since I can remember.

43
00:03:59.121 --> 00:04:01.681
Do you think that's normal?

44
00:04:01.724 --> 00:04:04.420
Don't most people
have different dreams?

45
00:04:05.094 --> 00:04:06.755
I don't know.

46
00:04:14.704 --> 00:04:18.105
There. You're beautiful.

47
00:04:18.541 --> 00:04:20.736
Now. can you manage a smile?

48
00:04:37.059 --> 00:04:40.119
At last. We thought you'd never arrive.

49
00:04:40.196 --> 00:04:44.098
Alice. Hamish is waiting
to dance with you. Go.

50
00:04:47.770 --> 00:04:50.102
You do realize it's well past 4:00.

51
00:04:50.139 --> 00:04:51.800
Now everything will have
to be rushed through.

52
00:04:51.874 --> 00:04:54.536
- I am sorry.
- Oh. never mind!

53
00:04:58.714 --> 00:05:02.878
Forgive my wife. She's been planning
this affair for over 20 years.

54
00:05:03.853 --> 00:05:06.083
If only Charles were here...

55
00:05:06.722 --> 00:05:08.280
My condolences.

56
00:05:08.958 --> 00:05:13.122
I think of your husband often.
He was truly a man of vision.

57
00:05:14.664 --> 00:05:18.293
I hope you don't think I've taken
advantage of your misfortunes.

58
00:05:18.334 --> 00:05:21.826
Of course not. I'm pleased
that you purchased the company.

59
00:05:23.239 --> 00:05:27.642
I was a fool for not investing in
his mad venture when I had the chance.

60
00:05:28.144 --> 00:05:30.112
Charles thought so. too.

61
00:05:49.098 --> 00:05:51.999
Hamish. do you ever tire of quadrille?

62
00:05:52.034 --> 00:05:55.060
On the contrary. I find it invigorating.

63
00:06:00.976 --> 00:06:02.466
Do I amuse you?

64
00:06:02.511 --> 00:06:03.603
No.

65
00:06:03.779 --> 00:06:06.805
I had a sudden vision
of all the ladies in trousers

66
00:06:06.849 --> 00:06:08.976
and the men wearing dresses.

67
00:06:09.118 --> 00:06:11.951
I think you'll do best
to keep your visions to yourself.

68
00:06:11.987 --> 00:06:14.455
When in doubt. remain silent.

69
00:06:22.531 --> 00:06:25.864
Pardon us. sir.
Miss Kingsleigh is distracted today.

70
00:06:26.102 --> 00:06:27.626
Where's your head?

71
00:06:27.703 --> 00:06:30.638
I was wondering
what it would be like to fly.

72
00:06:30.706 --> 00:06:31.764
Why would you spend your time

73
00:06:31.841 --> 00:06:34.036
thinking about
such an impossible thing?

74
00:06:34.076 --> 00:06:35.407
Why wouldn't I?

75
00:06:35.478 --> 00:06:38.743
My father said he sometimes believed
in six impossible things

76
00:06:38.814 --> 00:06:39.906
before breakfast.

77
00:06:42.918 --> 00:06:44.010
Come along.

78
00:06:46.756 --> 00:06:50.385
Alice. meet me under the gazebo
in precisely 10 minutes.

79
00:06:52.528 --> 00:06:54.223
We have a secret to tell you.

80
00:06:54.263 --> 00:06:56.322
If you're telling me.
then it's not much of a secret.

81
00:06:56.399 --> 00:06:58.924
- Perhaps we shouldn't.
- We decided we should.

82
00:06:58.968 --> 00:07:00.094
If we tell her. she won't be surprised.

83
00:07:00.136 --> 00:07:03.105
- Will you be surprised?
- Not if you tell me.

84
00:07:03.139 --> 00:07:04.936
But now you've brought it up.
you have to.

85
00:07:04.974 --> 00:07:07.568
- No. we don't.
- In fact. we won't.

86
00:07:09.111 --> 00:07:10.237
I wonder if your mother knows

87
00:07:10.279 --> 00:07:13.874
that you two swim naked
in the Havershims' pond.

88
00:07:13.916 --> 00:07:16.316
- You wouldn't.
- Oh. but I would.

89
00:07:16.919 --> 00:07:19.547
There's your mother right now.

90
00:07:19.588 --> 00:07:21.613
Hamish is going to ask for your hand.

91
00:07:21.657 --> 00:07:23.852
You've ruined the surprise!

92
00:07:24.727 --> 00:07:26.627
I could strangle them!

93
00:07:26.662 --> 00:07:29.825
Everyone went to so much effort
to keep the secret.

94
00:07:29.899 --> 00:07:31.526
Does everyone know?

95
00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:35.593
It's why they've all come.
This is your engagement party.

96
00:07:36.071 --> 00:07:39.700
Hamish will ask you under the gazebo.
When you say yes...

97
00:07:39.775 --> 00:07:42.335
But I don't know
if I want to marry Hamish.

98
00:07:42.411 --> 00:07:45.312
Who. then?
You won't do better than a lord.

99
00:07:48.651 --> 00:07:52.747
You'll soon be 20. Alice.
That pretty face won't last forever.

100
00:07:53.589 --> 00:07:56.786
You don't want to end up
like Aunt Imogene.

101
00:07:56.826 --> 00:07:59.226
And you don't want to be a burden
on Mother. do you?

102
00:07:59.295 --> 00:08:00.455
No.

103
00:08:00.496 --> 00:08:02.794
So you'll marry Hamish.

104
00:08:02.832 --> 00:08:04.629
You will be as happy
as I am with Lowell.

105
00:08:04.667 --> 00:08:06.157
and your life will be perfect.

106
00:08:06.335 --> 00:08:07.825
It's already decided.

107
00:08:07.870 --> 00:08:09.462
Alice. dear.

108
00:08:10.773 --> 00:08:12.468
I'll leave you to it.

109
00:08:12.508 --> 00:08:16.774
Shall we take a leisurely stroll
through the garden. just you and me?

110
00:08:21.750 --> 00:08:23.615
Do you know what I've always dreaded?

111
00:08:23.652 --> 00:08:25.552
The decline of the aristocracy?

112
00:08:25.988 --> 00:08:29.515
Ugly grandchildren. But you're lovely.

113
00:08:29.558 --> 00:08:33.050
You're bound to produce
little... Imbeciles!

114
00:08:33.128 --> 00:08:34.595
The gardeners have
planted white roses

115
00:08:34.663 --> 00:08:36.893
when I specifically asked for red.

116
00:08:36.966 --> 00:08:39.161
You could always paint the roses red.

117
00:08:39.201 --> 00:08:41.328
What an odd thing to say.

118
00:08:42.037 --> 00:08:45.837
You should know that my son
has extremely delicate digestion.

119
00:08:48.043 --> 00:08:50.477
- Did you see that?
- See what?

120
00:08:50.513 --> 00:08:53.175
- It was a rabbit. I think.
- Nasty things.

121
00:08:53.215 --> 00:08:55.911
I do enjoy setting the dogs on them.

122
00:08:56.452 --> 00:09:00.081
If you serve Hamish the wrong foods.
he could get a blockage.

123
00:09:01.357 --> 00:09:02.756
Did you see it that time?

124
00:09:02.825 --> 00:09:04.122
- See what?
- The rabbit.

125
00:09:04.193 --> 00:09:05.785
Don't shout.

126
00:09:05.861 --> 00:09:10.127
Now. pay attention.
Hamish said you were easily distracted.

127
00:09:10.199 --> 00:09:13.100
- What was I saying?
- Hamish has a blockage.

128
00:09:14.436 --> 00:09:18.202
I couldn't be more interested.
but you'll have to excuse me.

129
00:09:23.445 --> 00:09:24.912
Aunt Imogene.

130
00:09:26.048 --> 00:09:30.007
I think I'm going mad.
I keep seeing a rabbit in a waistcoat.

131
00:09:31.086 --> 00:09:33.680
I can't be bothered
with your fancy rabbit now.

132
00:09:33.722 --> 00:09:35.883
I'm waiting for my fianc�.

133
00:09:36.692 --> 00:09:38.489
- You have a fianc�?
- Hmm.

134
00:09:41.363 --> 00:09:43.593
There! Did you see it?

135
00:09:44.600 --> 00:09:46.124
He's a prince.

136
00:09:46.201 --> 00:09:50.729
But. alas. he cannot marry me
unless he renounces his throne.

137
00:09:51.273 --> 00:09:53.138
It's tragic. isn't it?

138
00:09:53.409 --> 00:09:54.637
Very.

139
00:10:04.587 --> 00:10:05.884
Lowell?

140
00:10:06.288 --> 00:10:08.756
Alice. We were just...

141
00:10:10.092 --> 00:10:11.923
Hattie's an old friend.

142
00:10:11.961 --> 00:10:13.952
I can see you're very close.

143
00:10:14.129 --> 00:10:17.030
Look. you won't mention this
to your sister. will you?

144
00:10:17.099 --> 00:10:21.433
I don't know. I'm confused.
I need time to think.

145
00:10:21.470 --> 00:10:25.634
Well. think about Margaret.
She'd never trust me again.

146
00:10:25.674 --> 00:10:27.801
You don't want to ruin her marriage.
do you?

147
00:10:27.843 --> 00:10:28.935
Me?

148
00:10:29.612 --> 00:10:33.571
But I'm not the one who's
sneaking around behind her back.

149
00:10:34.316 --> 00:10:35.840
There you are.

150
00:10:48.530 --> 00:10:50.293
Alice Kingsleigh...

151
00:10:50.666 --> 00:10:51.894
Hamish.

152
00:10:52.601 --> 00:10:53.659
What is it?

153
00:10:53.702 --> 00:10:56.466
You have a caterpillar
on your shoulder.

154
00:10:57.339 --> 00:10:58.465
Ew.

155
00:10:59.274 --> 00:11:00.798
Don't hurt it.

156
00:11:06.115 --> 00:11:08.481
You'll want to wash that finger.

157
00:11:13.355 --> 00:11:14.549
Alice Kingsleigh.

158
00:11:20.162 --> 00:11:21.993
will you be my wife?

159
00:11:25.634 --> 00:11:26.896
Well.

160
00:11:29.171 --> 00:11:31.230
everyone expects me to.

161
00:11:32.007 --> 00:11:34.498
and you're a lord.

162
00:11:35.678 --> 00:11:39.273
My face won't last.
and I don't want to end up like...

163
00:11:43.218 --> 00:11:45.982
But this is happening so quickly. I...

164
00:11:47.456 --> 00:11:48.980
I think I...

165
00:11:57.399 --> 00:11:58.957
I think I...

166
00:12:00.436 --> 00:12:02.131
I need a moment.

167
00:12:40.542 --> 00:12:41.736
Hello.

168
00:15:44.826 --> 00:15:46.691
It's only a dream.

169
00:16:28.704 --> 00:16:32.834
You'd think she would
remember all this from the first time.

170
00:16:34.309 --> 00:16:36.641
You've brought the wrong Alice.

171
00:16:36.678 --> 00:16:39.579
McTWISP: No. she's the right one.
I'm certain of it.

172
00:17:25.861 --> 00:17:27.795
She's the wrong Alice.

173
00:17:28.163 --> 00:17:29.858
McTWISP: Give her a chance.

174
00:18:47.008 --> 00:18:49.101
Curiouser and curiouser.

175
00:18:54.850 --> 00:18:56.977
I told you she's the right Alice.

176
00:18:57.018 --> 00:18:58.508
I am not convinced.

177
00:18:58.587 --> 00:19:00.111
McTWISP: How is that for gratitude?

178
00:19:00.155 --> 00:19:03.647
I've been up there for weeks.
trailing one Alice after the next.

179
00:19:03.725 --> 00:19:05.989
and I was almost eaten
by other animals.

180
00:19:06.061 --> 00:19:07.358
Can you imagine?

181
00:19:07.429 --> 00:19:12.196
<i>They go about entirely unclothed.
and they do their shukm in public.</i>

182
00:19:12.501 --> 00:19:14.969
- I had to avert my eyes.
- Doesn't look anything like herself.

183
00:19:15.003 --> 00:19:17.369
That's because she's the wrong Alice.

184
00:19:17.439 --> 00:19:20.203
- If she was. she might be.
- If she isn't. she ain't.

185
00:19:20.275 --> 00:19:23.301
- But if she were so. she would be.
- But she isn't. nohow.

186
00:19:23.345 --> 00:19:26.644
How can I be the wrong Alice
when this is my dream?

187
00:19:27.649 --> 00:19:29.674
And who are you. if I might ask?

188
00:19:29.718 --> 00:19:31.379
Oh. I'm Tweedledee. he's Tweedledum.

189
00:19:31.453 --> 00:19:33.478
Contrariwise. I'm Tweedledum.
he's Tweedledee.

190
00:19:33.522 --> 00:19:35.217
We should consult Absolem.

191
00:19:35.290 --> 00:19:37.656
Exactly. Absolem will know who she is.

192
00:19:37.692 --> 00:19:40.183
- I'll escort you.
- Hey. it's not being your turn.

193
00:19:40.228 --> 00:19:41.388
So unfair.

194
00:19:41.463 --> 00:19:43.226
- Hey. leave off!
- Let go!

195
00:19:43.298 --> 00:19:45.892
- Are they always this way?
- Family trait.

196
00:19:45.967 --> 00:19:47.867
You can both escort her.

197
00:19:55.877 --> 00:19:59.108
- Who is this Absolem?
- He's wise. He's absolute.

198
00:19:59.181 --> 00:20:00.876
He's Absolem.

199
00:20:24.940 --> 00:20:26.430
Who are you?

200
00:20:27.876 --> 00:20:29.138
Absolem?

201
00:20:29.211 --> 00:20:35.878
You're not Absolem. I'm Absolem.
The question is. who are you?

202
00:20:35.917 --> 00:20:37.714
Alice.

203
00:20:37.752 --> 00:20:39.276
We shall see.

204
00:20:39.721 --> 00:20:42.747
What do you mean by that?
I ought to know who I am.

205
00:20:42.824 --> 00:20:48.626
Yes. you ought. stupid girl.
Unroll the Oraculum.

206
00:20:54.569 --> 00:20:59.768
The Oraculum. being a calendrical
compendium of Underland.

207
00:21:03.144 --> 00:21:06.113
- It's a calendar.
- Compendium.

208
00:21:06.147 --> 00:21:11.107
It tells of each and every day
since the Beginning.

209
00:21:11.653 --> 00:21:16.056
Today is Griblig Day
in the time of the Red Queen.

210
00:21:17.892 --> 00:21:21.328
Show her the Frabjous Day.

211
00:21:21.463 --> 00:21:24.955
Mmm. Yeah. Frabjous being the day
you slay the Jabberwocky.

212
00:21:26.635 --> 00:21:28.694
Sorry? Slay a what?

213
00:21:28.770 --> 00:21:31.500
Oh. yeah. That being you. there.
with the Vorpal sword.

214
00:21:31.573 --> 00:21:34.508
No other swords can kill
the Jabberwocky. nohow.

215
00:21:34.576 --> 00:21:37.136
If it ain't Vorpal. it ain't dead.

216
00:21:37.779 --> 00:21:39.178
That's not me!

217
00:21:39.247 --> 00:21:40.544
I know!

218
00:21:41.182 --> 00:21:45.118
Resolve this for us. Absolem.
Is she the right Alice?

219
00:21:45.153 --> 00:21:47.348
Not hardly.

220
00:21:50.759 --> 00:21:53.250
- I told you.
- McTWISP: - Oh. dear.

221
00:21:53.295 --> 00:21:55.195
- I said so.
- I said so.

222
00:21:55.263 --> 00:21:56.855
Contrariwise.
you said she might be.

223
00:21:56.931 --> 00:21:58.831
No. you said she would be if she was.

224
00:21:58.867 --> 00:22:02.860
Little impostor. Pretending
to be Alice. She should be ashamed.

225
00:22:02.937 --> 00:22:04.871
I was so certain of you.

226
00:22:04.939 --> 00:22:07.965
I'm sorry.
I don't mean to be the wrong Alice.

227
00:22:08.777 --> 00:22:11.974
Wait. this is my dream.

228
00:22:12.347 --> 00:22:15.874
I'm going to wake up now
and you'll all disappear.

229
00:22:23.491 --> 00:22:26.551
That's odd.
Pinching usually does the trick.

230
00:22:26.995 --> 00:22:28.895
I could stick you. if that would help.

231
00:22:29.197 --> 00:22:32.189
- It might. actually. Thank you.
- My pleasure.

232
00:22:32.801 --> 00:22:33.893
Ow!

233
00:22:37.339 --> 00:22:39.569
- Bandersnatch!
- Bandersnatch!

234
00:23:29.257 --> 00:23:30.519
Wait.

235
00:23:33.395 --> 00:23:36.455
It's only a dream. Nothing can hurt me.

236
00:23:41.136 --> 00:23:42.228
What's she doing?

237
00:23:42.470 --> 00:23:44.961
Can't hurt me. Can't hurt me.

238
00:23:50.779 --> 00:23:52.269
Run. you great lug!

239
00:24:57.145 --> 00:24:58.976
This way. east to Queast.

240
00:24:59.013 --> 00:25:00.571
No. south to Snud.

241
00:25:00.648 --> 00:25:02.172
No. No. no. This way.

242
00:25:50.331 --> 00:25:53.698
Someone has stolen three of my tarts!

243
00:26:01.910 --> 00:26:04.777
- Did you steal them?
- No. Your Majesty.

244
00:26:04.846 --> 00:26:06.746
- Did you?
- No. Your Majesty.

245
00:26:06.781 --> 00:26:09.272
- Did you steal them?
- No. Your Majesty.

246
00:26:42.250 --> 00:26:44.184
Did you steal my tarts?

247
00:26:45.119 --> 00:26:46.848
No. Your Majesty.

248
00:26:53.561 --> 00:26:55.222
Squimberry juice.

249
00:26:55.530 --> 00:26:58.328
- I was so hungry! I didn't mean to!
- Off with his head!

250
00:26:58.399 --> 00:27:00.629
My family! Oh. please. please don't!

251
00:27:00.668 --> 00:27:02.829
No! I have little ones to look after!

252
00:27:02.904 --> 00:27:04.428
Go to his house
and collect the little ones.

253
00:27:04.472 --> 00:27:06.804
I love tadpoles on toast
almost as much as I love caviar.

254
00:27:06.841 --> 00:27:08.638
Yes. Your Majesty.

255
00:27:12.280 --> 00:27:13.645
Drink!

256
00:27:18.753 --> 00:27:20.050
Majesty?

257
00:27:22.523 --> 00:27:27.961
Ilosovic Stayne. you knave.
where have you been lurking?

258
00:27:28.930 --> 00:27:34.664
Majesty. I have found the Oraculum.

259
00:27:37.038 --> 00:27:40.235
That? Looks so ordinary for an oracle.

260
00:27:40.308 --> 00:27:42.970
Look here. on the Frabjous Day.

261
00:27:46.147 --> 00:27:49.048
I'd know that tangled mess
of hair anywhere.

262
00:27:49.217 --> 00:27:50.707
Is it Alice?

263
00:27:51.152 --> 00:27:52.847
I believe it is.

264
00:27:53.621 --> 00:27:56.021
What's she doing
with my darling Jabberwocky?

265
00:27:56.057 --> 00:27:58.321
She appears to be slaying it.

266
00:27:59.093 --> 00:28:01.391
She killed my Jabber-baby-wocky?

267
00:28:01.462 --> 00:28:06.195
Not yet. but it will happen
if we don't stop her.

268
00:28:06.801 --> 00:28:09.668
Find Alice. Stayne. Find her!

269
00:28:12.173 --> 00:28:15.438
Find the scent of human girl
and earn your freedom.

270
00:28:15.610 --> 00:28:17.908
For my wife and pups. as well?

271
00:28:20.014 --> 00:28:21.982
Everyone will go home.

272
00:28:35.396 --> 00:28:38.388
Dogs will believe anything.

273
00:29:10.732 --> 00:29:15.931
It looks like you ran afoul of something
with wicked claws.

274
00:29:16.738 --> 00:29:18.262
And I'm still dreaming.

275
00:29:18.306 --> 00:29:20.274
What did that to you?

276
00:29:20.808 --> 00:29:24.107
- Banner or Bander...
- The Bandersnatch?

277
00:29:24.445 --> 00:29:26.879
Well. I'd better have a look.

278
00:29:27.348 --> 00:29:28.645
What are you doing?

279
00:29:28.683 --> 00:29:32.449
It needs to be purified
by someone with evaporating skills.

280
00:29:32.487 --> 00:29:35.684
or it will fester and putrefy.

281
00:29:36.591 --> 00:29:40.527
I'd rather you didn't.
I'll be fine as soon as I wake up.

282
00:29:40.595 --> 00:29:43.496
At least let me bind it for you.

283
00:29:44.766 --> 00:29:48.202
- What do you call yourself?
- Alice.

284
00:29:48.269 --> 00:29:50.134
The Alice?

285
00:29:51.172 --> 00:29:55.632
- There's been some debate about that.
- I never get involved in politics.

286
00:29:56.010 --> 00:29:58.035
You'd best be on your way.

287
00:29:58.613 --> 00:30:02.640
What way? All I want to do is
wake up from this dream.

288
00:30:02.850 --> 00:30:04.249
Fine.

289
00:30:04.318 --> 00:30:08.914
Then I'll take you to the Hare
and the Hatter. but that's the end of it.

290
00:30:17.465 --> 00:30:18.830
Coming?

291
00:31:09.283 --> 00:31:10.409
Watch what you're doing!

292
00:31:10.451 --> 00:31:11.941
Hey. watch it!

293
00:31:15.289 --> 00:31:16.881
Okay. okay. All right.

294
00:31:16.924 --> 00:31:18.391
It's you.

295
00:31:18.426 --> 00:31:22.021
No. it's not.
McTwisp brought us the wrong Alice.

296
00:31:22.063 --> 00:31:23.724
It's the wrong Alice!

297
00:31:23.764 --> 00:31:25.629
It's absolutely Alice.

298
00:31:25.700 --> 00:31:28.635
You're absolutely Alice.
I'd know you anywhere.

299
00:31:28.703 --> 00:31:30.637
I'd know him anywhere.

300
00:31:32.773 --> 00:31:35.571
Well. as you can see.
we're still having tea.

301
00:31:35.610 --> 00:31:39.410
And it's all because I was obliged
to kill Time waiting for your return.

302
00:31:39.447 --> 00:31:42.280
You're terribly late. you know. Naughty.

303
00:31:42.884 --> 00:31:46.445
Well. anyway. Time became
quite offended and stopped altogether.

304
00:31:46.487 --> 00:31:48.011
Not a tick ever since.

305
00:31:50.324 --> 00:31:52.349
- Cup.
- Time can be funny in dreams.

306
00:31:52.426 --> 00:31:54.360
Yes. yes. of course.
but now you're back. you see.

307
00:31:54.428 --> 00:31:56.328
and we need to get on
to the Frabjous Day.

308
00:31:56.397 --> 00:31:58.331
- Frabjous Day!
- Frabjous Day!

309
00:31:58.399 --> 00:32:01.857
I'm investigating things
that begin with the letter "M."

310
00:32:03.271 --> 00:32:06.104
Have you any idea
why a raven is like a writing desk?

311
00:32:07.275 --> 00:32:08.970
<i>- Downal wyth Bluddy Behg Hid!
- Downal wyth Bluddy Behg Hid!</i>

312
00:32:09.010 --> 00:32:11.444
- What?
- Down with the Bloody Big Head.

313
00:32:11.479 --> 00:32:13.970
the Bloody Big Head
being the Red Queen.

314
00:32:14.015 --> 00:32:16.779
Come. come. We simply must
commence with the slaying and such.

315
00:32:16.817 --> 00:32:18.785
Therefore. it is high time
to forgive and forget

316
00:32:18.819 --> 00:32:20.787
or forget and forgive.
whichever comes first

317
00:32:20.821 --> 00:32:24.120
or is. in any case. most convenient.
I'm waiting.

318
00:32:24.158 --> 00:32:26.626
Hey.
It's tick-tick... It's ticking again.

319
00:32:26.661 --> 00:32:31.155
All this talk of blood and slaying
has put me off my tea.

320
00:32:31.432 --> 00:32:32.524
Ah.

321
00:32:33.434 --> 00:32:38.565
The entire world is falling to ruin
and poor Chessur's off his tea.

322
00:32:38.940 --> 00:32:41.807
What happened that day
was not my fault.

323
00:32:44.145 --> 00:32:46.136
Oh. dear.

324
00:32:47.148 --> 00:32:49.810
You ran out on them
to save your own skin.

325
00:32:49.951 --> 00:32:51.885
<i>you guddler's scuttish pilgar lickering</i>

326
00:32:51.953 --> 00:32:54.080
<i>shukm juggling sluking urpal.</i>

327
00:32:54.155 --> 00:32:55.850
<i>Bar lom muck egg brimni!</i>

328
00:32:55.890 --> 00:32:57.187
Hatter!

329
00:32:58.225 --> 00:33:00.420
- Thank you.
- Meow.

330
00:33:00.962 --> 00:33:02.054
I'm fine.

331
00:33:02.129 --> 00:33:05.565
What's wrong with you. Tarrant?
You used to be the life of the party.

332
00:33:05.633 --> 00:33:08.659
You used to do the best Futterwacken
in all of Witzend.

333
00:33:08.703 --> 00:33:11.001
- Futter what?
- Futterwacken!

334
00:33:11.038 --> 00:33:12.164
It's a dance.

335
00:33:13.341 --> 00:33:16.037
On the Frabjous Day.

336
00:33:16.077 --> 00:33:19.672
when the White Queen
once again wears the crown.

337
00:33:19.714 --> 00:33:25.675
on that day.
I shall Futterwacken vigorously.

338
00:33:28.723 --> 00:33:30.020
Oh. no.

339
00:33:31.492 --> 00:33:32.857
Uh-oh.

340
00:33:33.728 --> 00:33:35.753
The Knave.

341
00:33:35.830 --> 00:33:37.024
Goodbye.

342
00:33:37.565 --> 00:33:39.226
Hide her!

343
00:33:39.266 --> 00:33:40.961
Drink this quickly.

344
00:33:42.870 --> 00:33:44.929
Quick! Hide her!

345
00:33:48.009 --> 00:33:49.442
Oh. dear.

346
00:33:53.514 --> 00:33:54.606
Aye.

347
00:33:56.951 --> 00:33:58.475
Mind your head.

348
00:34:12.600 --> 00:34:13.726
Let me out!

349
00:34:16.570 --> 00:34:22.668
Well. if it's not my favorite
trio of lunatics.

350
00:34:23.144 --> 00:34:25.237
Would you like to join us?

351
00:34:26.447 --> 00:34:28.438
You're all late for tea!

352
00:34:33.220 --> 00:34:37.418
We're looking for the girl called Alice.

353
00:34:38.159 --> 00:34:41.185
Speaking of the Queen. here is a little
song we used to sing in her honor.

354
00:34:42.396 --> 00:34:44.387
<i>- Twinkle Twinkle little bat
- Twinkle Twinkle little bat</i>

355
00:34:44.432 --> 00:34:46.593
<i>- How I wonder where you're at
- How I wonder where you're at</i>

356
00:34:46.634 --> 00:34:48.602
<i>- Up a...
- Up a...</i>

357
00:34:48.636 --> 00:34:52.800
If you're hiding her.
you'll lose your heads.

358
00:34:52.907 --> 00:34:54.602
Already lost them.

359
00:34:56.010 --> 00:34:57.341
All together now!

360
00:34:57.411 --> 00:34:59.436
<i>- Up above the world you fly
- Up above the world you fly</i>

361
00:34:59.480 --> 00:35:01.778
<i>- Like a tea tray in the sky
- Like a tea tray in the sky</i>

362
00:35:01.816 --> 00:35:04.444
<i>- Twinkle. twinkle. twinkle. twinkle
- Twinkle. twinkle. twinkle. twinkle</i>

363
00:35:04.485 --> 00:35:06.544
<i>- Twinkle. twinkle. twinkle
- Twinkle. twinkle. twinkle</i>

364
00:35:06.620 --> 00:35:08.781
<i>- Twinkle. twinkle. twinkle...
- Twinkle. twinkle. twinkle...</i>

365
00:35:09.090 --> 00:35:10.182
Oh!

366
00:35:14.595 --> 00:35:16.859
<i>Downal wyth Bluddy Behg Hid!</i>

367
00:35:20.835 --> 00:35:22.894
Would you like some cream?

368
00:35:26.373 --> 00:35:29.240
- Would you like a slice of Battenberg?
- Follow the bloodhound.

369
00:35:30.444 --> 00:35:32.241
- Sugar?
- Yes. please.

370
00:35:33.447 --> 00:35:36.314
- Oh. that's lovely.
- You're all mad.

371
00:35:36.550 --> 00:35:38.347
Thanks very much.

372
00:35:40.221 --> 00:35:41.984
Pass the scones. please.

373
00:35:44.959 --> 00:35:46.392
- That one there.
- Oh! Pardon.

374
00:35:46.460 --> 00:35:48.519
- Yes.
- Yep. aye.

375
00:35:48.562 --> 00:35:50.029
One moment.

376
00:35:58.139 --> 00:35:59.902
There. Yes.

377
00:36:00.141 --> 00:36:01.938
Try this on for size.

378
00:36:08.482 --> 00:36:09.779
Oh.

379
00:36:13.654 --> 00:36:14.916
I like it.

380
00:36:14.989 --> 00:36:18.618
Good thing the bloodhound
is one of us. or you'd be...

381
00:36:18.692 --> 00:36:20.353
What do they want with me?

382
00:36:20.394 --> 00:36:22.419
Wait a minute.
best take her to the White Queen.

383
00:36:22.496 --> 00:36:25.192
She'll be safe there. Spoon...

384
00:36:27.401 --> 00:36:29.301
Your carriage. milady.

385
00:36:29.670 --> 00:36:31.797
- The hat?
- Of course.

386
00:36:31.872 --> 00:36:33.737
Anyone can go by horse or rail.

387
00:36:33.774 --> 00:36:38.871
but the absolute best way to travel
is by hat. Have I made a rhyme?

388
00:36:40.047 --> 00:36:42.208
Oh. I love traveling by hat.

389
00:36:42.249 --> 00:36:45.446
Mally. Just Alice. please.
Fairfarren. all.

390
00:36:45.753 --> 00:36:47.914
What do you mean? Wait. Gae!

391
00:36:53.527 --> 00:36:59.090
"'Twas brillig. and the slithy toves
Did gyre and gimble in the wabe

392
00:36:59.166 --> 00:37:03.068
"All mimsy were the borogoves
And the mome raths outgrabe"

393
00:37:03.103 --> 00:37:04.934
Sorry. what was that?

394
00:37:05.806 --> 00:37:07.398
What was what?

395
00:37:10.044 --> 00:37:15.346
"The Jabberwock. with eyes of flame
Jaws that bite and claws that catch!

396
00:37:15.416 --> 00:37:19.785
"'Beware the Jabberwock. my son!
And the frumious Bandersnatch! '

397
00:37:21.422 --> 00:37:26.917
"He took his Vorpal sword in hand
The Vorpal blade went snicker-snack!

398
00:37:26.961 --> 00:37:32.263
"He left it dead. and with its head
He went galumphing back"

399
00:37:34.568 --> 00:37:36.934
It's all about you. you know.

400
00:37:37.238 --> 00:37:41.800
I'm not slaying anything.
I don't slay. so put it out of your mind.

401
00:37:46.614 --> 00:37:47.876
Mind.

402
00:37:54.655 --> 00:37:57.021
Wait! You can't leave me here!

403
00:38:00.160 --> 00:38:01.855
You don't slay.

404
00:38:02.463 --> 00:38:05.523
Do you have any idea
what the Red Queen has done?

405
00:38:05.599 --> 00:38:07.294
You don't slay.

406
00:38:07.768 --> 00:38:09.895
I couldn't if I wanted to.

407
00:38:12.172 --> 00:38:14.834
You're not the same
as you were before.

408
00:38:15.175 --> 00:38:20.238
You were much more muchier.
You've lost your muchness.

409
00:38:21.148 --> 00:38:22.706
My "muchness"?

410
00:38:23.284 --> 00:38:25.684
In there. Something's missing.

411
00:38:26.287 --> 00:38:28.721
Tell me what Red Queen has done.

412
00:38:31.225 --> 00:38:33.216
It's not a pretty story.

413
00:38:33.861 --> 00:38:35.419
Tell me anyway.

414
00:38:47.041 --> 00:38:48.838
It was here.

415
00:38:49.843 --> 00:38:52.835
I was hatter to the White Queen
at the time.

416
00:38:54.014 --> 00:38:57.347
Hightopp clan have always
been employed at court.

417
00:40:48.929 --> 00:40:51.295
Hatter? Hatter!

418
00:40:52.466 --> 00:40:53.865
I'm fine.

419
00:40:54.802 --> 00:40:56.064
Are you?

420
00:40:58.872 --> 00:41:02.171
Did you hear that?
I'm certain I heard something.

421
00:41:02.976 --> 00:41:04.034
What?

422
00:41:05.212 --> 00:41:06.679
Oh! Red Knights.

423
00:41:42.082 --> 00:41:43.674
Go south to Trotter's Bottom.

424
00:41:43.717 --> 00:41:46.277
The White Queen's castle
is just beyond.

425
00:41:46.353 --> 00:41:48.014
Hold on tightly.

426
00:41:51.758 --> 00:41:54.090
Down with the bloody Red Queen!

427
00:42:54.454 --> 00:42:57.617
You were supposed to lead them away!
The Hatter trusted you!

428
00:42:57.658 --> 00:42:59.785
They have my wife and pups.

429
00:43:00.327 --> 00:43:02.625
- What's your name?
- Bayard.

430
00:43:03.063 --> 00:43:04.121
Sit!

431
00:43:06.400 --> 00:43:09.494
Would your name be Alice.
by any chance?

432
00:43:09.536 --> 00:43:12.266
Yes. but I'm not the one
that everyone's talking about.

433
00:43:12.306 --> 00:43:15.935
The Hatter would not have
given himself up just for any Alice.

434
00:43:15.976 --> 00:43:17.637
Where did they take him?

435
00:43:17.678 --> 00:43:21.045
To the Red Queen's castle
at Salazen Grum.

436
00:43:21.114 --> 00:43:23.139
We're going to rescue him.

437
00:43:23.183 --> 00:43:24.650
That is not foretold.

438
00:43:24.685 --> 00:43:28.451
I don't care.
He wouldn't be there if it weren't for me.

439
00:43:28.488 --> 00:43:31.150
The Frabjous Day is almost upon us.

440
00:43:31.191 --> 00:43:33.819
You must prepare
to meet the Jabberwocky.

441
00:43:33.860 --> 00:43:35.794
From the moment
I fell down that rabbit hole.

442
00:43:35.829 --> 00:43:38.662
I've been told what I must do
and who I must be.

443
00:43:38.699 --> 00:43:42.658
I've been shrunk. stretched. scratched
and stuffed into a teapot.

444
00:43:42.736 --> 00:43:46.968
I've been accused of being Alice and
of not being Alice. but this is my dream.

445
00:43:47.007 --> 00:43:49.168
I'll decide where it goes from here.

446
00:43:49.209 --> 00:43:51.006
If you diverge from the path...

447
00:43:51.044 --> 00:43:52.841
I make the path.

448
00:44:04.024 --> 00:44:07.687
Take me to Salazen Grum. Bayard.
and don't forget the hat.

449
00:44:54.541 --> 00:44:56.270
There's only one way across.

450
00:45:02.549 --> 00:45:04.779
Lost my muchness. have I?

451
00:45:48.662 --> 00:45:50.357
Bayard! The hat!

452
00:46:20.327 --> 00:46:21.885
Your Majesty.

453
00:46:30.904 --> 00:46:32.371
So sorry.

454
00:46:41.681 --> 00:46:43.171
Splendid shot!

455
00:46:46.486 --> 00:46:48.351
Where's my ball? Page!

456
00:46:49.022 --> 00:46:50.080
Yes. Your Majesty.

457
00:46:53.160 --> 00:46:54.889
I want to help you.

458
00:47:00.033 --> 00:47:02.524
Well. if it isn't the wrong Alice.

459
00:47:03.703 --> 00:47:05.728
What brings you here? Mmm?

460
00:47:05.772 --> 00:47:07.433
I've come to rescue the Hatter.

461
00:47:07.507 --> 00:47:10.203
You're not rescuing anyone
being the size of a gerbil.

462
00:47:10.243 --> 00:47:13.007
Well. do you have any more
of that cake that made me grow before?

463
00:47:13.046 --> 00:47:16.015
Upelkuchen?
Actually. I might have some left.

464
00:47:25.525 --> 00:47:27.117
Not all of it!

465
00:47:27.594 --> 00:47:30.893
Oh. no! Stop! No. no. no. don't.
Don't do that!

466
00:47:32.332 --> 00:47:33.526
Page!

467
00:47:34.868 --> 00:47:36.233
Oh. dear.

468
00:47:41.675 --> 00:47:43.575
And what is this?

469
00:47:43.610 --> 00:47:47.706
It... It's a "who." Majesty. This is. um...

470
00:47:49.182 --> 00:47:50.274
Um?

471
00:47:51.351 --> 00:47:53.376
From Umbradge.

472
00:47:53.420 --> 00:47:55.615
What happened to your clothes?

473
00:47:55.689 --> 00:47:59.887
I outgrew them.
I've been growing an awful lot lately.

474
00:47:59.926 --> 00:48:04.761
I tower over everyone in Umbradge.
They laugh at me.

475
00:48:04.798 --> 00:48:08.097
So I've come to you. hoping you might
understand what it's like.

476
00:48:08.134 --> 00:48:09.658
My dear girl.

477
00:48:09.736 --> 00:48:13.297
anyone with a head that large
is welcome in my court.

478
00:48:13.340 --> 00:48:14.602
Someone find her some clothes!

479
00:48:14.641 --> 00:48:18.441
Use the curtains if you must.
but clothe this enormous girl.

480
00:48:27.921 --> 00:48:29.616
I need a pig here!

481
00:48:35.262 --> 00:48:38.425
I love a warm pig belly
for my aching feet.

482
00:48:38.465 --> 00:48:41.195
- Would you like one. Um?
- No. thank you.

483
00:48:41.268 --> 00:48:42.530
Sit!

484
00:48:44.938 --> 00:48:46.166
Sit!

485
00:48:49.809 --> 00:48:51.106
Go away.

486
00:48:54.281 --> 00:48:57.307
Where are my fat boys?
You must meet them.

487
00:48:57.417 --> 00:48:58.679
Fat boys!

488
00:49:01.087 --> 00:49:04.454
Oh. There they are.
Aren't they adorable?

489
00:49:04.491 --> 00:49:08.325
They have the oddest way of speaking.
Speak. boys. Amuse us.

490
00:49:09.362 --> 00:49:11.125
Go on.

491
00:49:13.934 --> 00:49:15.128
No.

492
00:49:15.168 --> 00:49:16.328
Speak!

493
00:49:17.771 --> 00:49:20.706
- Is that being...
- No. no. it isn't. Not a bit. No.

494
00:49:20.740 --> 00:49:22.537
Contrariwise. I believe it's so.

495
00:49:22.609 --> 00:49:24.634
No. it ain't so. nohow!

496
00:49:28.014 --> 00:49:30.812
I love my fat boys. Now. get out.

497
00:49:39.326 --> 00:49:41.851
- He did pinch me.
- He did pinch me.

498
00:50:00.513 --> 00:50:04.279
And who is this lovely creature?

499
00:50:07.087 --> 00:50:08.714
Um. my new favorite.

500
00:50:08.755 --> 00:50:10.586
- Well. does she have a name?
- Um.

501
00:50:10.657 --> 00:50:13.854
I believe your name
has slipped the Queen's mind.

502
00:50:13.893 --> 00:50:15.952
Her name is Um. idiot!

503
00:50:17.764 --> 00:50:19.459
From Umbradge.

504
00:50:19.532 --> 00:50:21.124
Any luck with the prisoner?

505
00:50:21.201 --> 00:50:22.759
He's stubborn.

506
00:50:23.703 --> 00:50:26.934
You're too soft. Bring him!

507
00:50:51.031 --> 00:50:53.397
We know Alice has returned
to Underland.

508
00:50:53.433 --> 00:50:55.424
Do you know where she is?

509
00:50:57.404 --> 00:51:01.170
I've been considering things
that begin with the letter "M."

510
00:51:01.674 --> 00:51:08.443
Moron. mutiny. murder. malice.

511
00:51:08.715 --> 00:51:12.014
We're looking for an "A" word now.
Where is Alice?

512
00:51:13.086 --> 00:51:16.453
Who. that wee little boy?
I wouldn't know.

513
00:51:17.624 --> 00:51:19.683
What if I take off your head?
Will you know then?

514
00:51:21.594 --> 00:51:22.959
Stop that.

515
00:51:23.930 --> 00:51:27.093
What a regrettably large head
you have.

516
00:51:27.133 --> 00:51:29.294
I should very much like to hat it.

517
00:51:29.335 --> 00:51:30.825
- Hat it?
- Yes.

518
00:51:31.471 --> 00:51:33.735
I used to hat
the White Queen. you know.

519
00:51:33.807 --> 00:51:35.638
Wasn't very much to work with.
poor dear.

520
00:51:35.675 --> 00:51:37.472
Her head is so small.

521
00:51:37.811 --> 00:51:40.211
It's tiny. It's a pimple of a head.

522
00:51:40.280 --> 00:51:41.645
But this...

523
00:51:42.348 --> 00:51:48.446
What I could do
with this monument. this orb...

524
00:51:48.955 --> 00:51:53.824
Nay. this magnificently heroic globe.

525
00:51:57.464 --> 00:51:59.159
What could you do?

526
00:52:01.034 --> 00:52:02.831
Unbind him. Stayne.

527
00:52:03.369 --> 00:52:06.065
How can he work
if his hands are bound?

528
00:52:14.547 --> 00:52:17.573
Well. then.
shall it be a bonnet or a boater?

529
00:52:18.485 --> 00:52:20.680
Or something for the boudoir?

530
00:52:21.488 --> 00:52:27.723
Cloche. dunce hat. death cap. coif.
snood. barboosh. pugree. yarmulke.

531
00:52:27.794 --> 00:52:31.161
cockle hat. porkpie. tam o'shanter.
billycock. bicorne. tricorne. bandeau.

532
00:52:31.197 --> 00:52:32.824
bongrace. fan-tail. night cap.
Garibaldi. fez...

533
00:52:32.866 --> 00:52:34.094
Hatter.

534
00:52:34.634 --> 00:52:35.692
Fez?

535
00:52:39.906 --> 00:52:41.237
Leave us.

536
00:52:53.887 --> 00:52:55.411
The trees seem sad.

537
00:52:55.488 --> 00:52:58.457
- Have you been speaking with them?
- Yes. Your Majesty.

538
00:52:58.525 --> 00:53:00.584
Perhaps a bit more kindly.

539
00:53:03.696 --> 00:53:06.859
Would you all excuse me
for a moment? Thank you.

540
00:53:17.210 --> 00:53:21.078
- What news. Bayard?
- Alice has returned to Underland.

541
00:53:21.848 --> 00:53:24.942
- Where is she now?
- In Salazen Grum.

542
00:53:25.552 --> 00:53:29.579
Forgive me. I allowed her
to divert from her destined path.

543
00:53:29.622 --> 00:53:34.321
No. no. no. no. But that is exactly
where she will find the Vorpal sword.

544
00:53:35.128 --> 00:53:38.825
We have our champion.
Rest now. You've done well.

545
00:53:57.250 --> 00:53:59.616
Have you seen
a hat around here?

546
00:54:12.932 --> 00:54:14.763
You must find Alice. Stayne.

547
00:54:14.801 --> 00:54:15.859
Without the Jabberwocky.

548
00:54:15.935 --> 00:54:19.200
my sister's followers
will surely rise against me.

549
00:54:20.106 --> 00:54:23.337
Ugly little sister.
Why do they adore her and not me?

550
00:54:23.676 --> 00:54:30.138
I cannot fathom it.
You are far superior in all ways.

551
00:54:30.483 --> 00:54:31.950
I know.

552
00:54:31.985 --> 00:54:35.045
But Mirana can make anyone
fall in love with her.

553
00:54:35.121 --> 00:54:37.282
Men. women.

554
00:54:41.494 --> 00:54:43.291
even the furniture.

555
00:54:45.198 --> 00:54:47.029
Even the King?

556
00:54:54.474 --> 00:54:57.238
I had to do it. He would have left me.

557
00:54:59.646 --> 00:55:06.176
Majesty. is it not better
to be feared than loved?

558
00:55:08.388 --> 00:55:10.219
Not certain anymore.

559
00:55:11.991 --> 00:55:15.188
Oh. let her have the rabble.
I don't need them.

560
00:55:15.895 --> 00:55:17.328
I have you.

561
00:55:36.983 --> 00:55:38.610
They're wonderful.

562
00:55:40.486 --> 00:55:42.750
You must let me try one on.

563
00:55:42.822 --> 00:55:45.723
It is good to be working
at my trade again.

564
00:55:47.060 --> 00:55:50.188
It's just a pity
you have to make them for her.

565
00:55:54.867 --> 00:55:57.062
What is the hatter with me?

566
00:55:58.371 --> 00:55:59.599
Hatter?

567
00:56:10.616 --> 00:56:11.913
Hatter.

568
00:56:13.753 --> 00:56:17.154
Have you any idea
why a raven is like a writing desk?

569
00:56:18.191 --> 00:56:19.988
I'm frightened. Alice.

570
00:56:20.259 --> 00:56:23.387
I don't like it in here.
It's terribly crowded.

571
00:56:26.799 --> 00:56:28.426
Have I gone mad?

572
00:56:33.239 --> 00:56:36.470
I'm afraid so. You're entirely bonkers.

573
00:56:38.211 --> 00:56:42.011
But I'll tell you a secret.
All the best people are.

574
00:56:49.789 --> 00:56:50.949
Here.

575
00:56:54.394 --> 00:56:57.158
That's better. You look yourself again.

576
00:57:00.266 --> 00:57:02.029
Hat man!
Where are my hats?

577
00:57:02.101 --> 00:57:03.796
I'm not a patient monarch!

578
00:57:03.836 --> 00:57:06.396
I'm told she keeps the Vorpal sword
hidden in the castle.

579
00:57:06.472 --> 00:57:08.337
The rabbit will help you.

580
00:57:08.374 --> 00:57:11.639
Find it. Alice.
Take it to the White Queen.

581
00:57:11.677 --> 00:57:13.611
We'll go to the White Queen together.

582
00:57:13.646 --> 00:57:17.480
Why is it you're always too small
or too tall?

583
00:57:30.296 --> 00:57:32.025
- Tweedles.
- Alice.

584
00:57:32.098 --> 00:57:34.362
- How do you do. again?
- Where's the rabbit?

585
00:57:34.434 --> 00:57:36.368
How is it you're being so great big?

586
00:57:36.402 --> 00:57:38.597
She ain't great big.
this is how she normal is.

587
00:57:38.671 --> 00:57:40.832
I'm certain she's smaller when we met.

588
00:57:40.873 --> 00:57:44.673
No. she drank the pishsalver
to get through the door. recall it?

589
00:57:44.710 --> 00:57:45.802
Oh. yeah.

590
00:57:45.845 --> 00:57:47.745
- Where's the rabbit?
- Over theres.

591
00:57:57.056 --> 00:57:59.650
- What are you doing here?
- I'm rescuing the Hatter.

592
00:57:59.692 --> 00:58:01.159
I'm rescuing the Hatter.

593
00:58:01.194 --> 00:58:04.994
He told me that the Vorpal sword
is hidden in the castle. Help me find it.

594
00:58:05.031 --> 00:58:07.932
I don't take orders
from big. clumsy. galumphing...

595
00:58:08.000 --> 00:58:09.092
Shoo!

596
00:58:13.239 --> 00:58:16.834
- What is it. McTwisp?
- I know where the sword is.

597
00:58:23.382 --> 00:58:25.441
The sword's hidden inside.

598
00:58:27.053 --> 00:58:28.850
Be careful. Alice.

599
00:58:38.531 --> 00:58:40.226
I know that smell.

600
00:58:49.575 --> 00:58:51.543
I'm not going in there.

601
00:58:52.545 --> 00:58:54.979
Look what that thing did to my arm.

602
00:58:55.047 --> 00:58:58.744
Dear. oh. dear.
Why haven't you mentioned this?

603
00:58:58.784 --> 00:59:00.809
It wasn't this bad before.

604
00:59:16.469 --> 00:59:19.961
Hatter? Where are you?

605
00:59:21.841 --> 00:59:23.103
Hatter?

606
00:59:24.043 --> 00:59:25.101
Mallymkun.

607
00:59:26.045 --> 00:59:28.445
Do you still have
the Bandersnatch eye?

608
00:59:28.481 --> 00:59:29.846
Right here.

609
00:59:30.583 --> 00:59:32.915
- I need it.
- Come and get it.

610
00:59:34.954 --> 00:59:36.649
Hey! Give it back!

611
00:59:49.335 --> 00:59:50.893
I like you. Um.

612
00:59:52.772 --> 00:59:54.967
I like largeness.

613
00:59:56.242 --> 00:59:57.971
Get away from me.

614
01:00:15.361 --> 01:00:17.022
I have your eye.

615
01:01:29.935 --> 01:01:31.061
No.

616
01:01:34.073 --> 01:01:35.131
Hmm.

617
01:01:35.207 --> 01:01:37.471
You look stunning in that hat.

618
01:01:37.543 --> 01:01:39.374
Yes. Next.

619
01:01:43.282 --> 01:01:45.910
Your Majesty has never looked better.

620
01:01:46.419 --> 01:01:48.080
Hmm. Another.

621
01:01:55.895 --> 01:01:56.953
Oh!

622
01:01:58.764 --> 01:02:00.789
I don't wish to alarm you.

623
01:02:00.900 --> 01:02:04.461
but it smells as though
you might have dropped something.

624
01:02:16.716 --> 01:02:19.276
Never mind him. he's mad.
Come along.

625
01:02:25.424 --> 01:02:28.325
Stayne!

626
01:03:22.481 --> 01:03:24.972
I suppose this makes us even now.

627
01:04:05.424 --> 01:04:06.891
Um forced herself on me.

628
01:04:06.926 --> 01:04:13.422
I told her my heart belongs to you.
but she's obsessed with me.

629
01:04:19.205 --> 01:04:20.900
Off with her head!

630
01:04:23.909 --> 01:04:26.070
Stand back. Mallymkun.

631
01:04:26.111 --> 01:04:27.442
How's this for muchness?

632
01:04:27.513 --> 01:04:29.208
No. no!
It mustn't be used for anything...

633
01:04:31.383 --> 01:04:34.284
Arrest that girl for unlawful seduction!

634
01:04:35.087 --> 01:04:36.384
Hatter!

635
01:04:38.290 --> 01:04:40.622
- Take it to the White Queen.
- I'm not leaving without you.

636
01:04:40.693 --> 01:04:41.887
Go!

637
01:05:08.420 --> 01:05:10.047
Run. Alice!

638
01:05:13.259 --> 01:05:14.453
Alice?

639
01:05:15.661 --> 01:05:16.787
Run!

640
01:05:22.501 --> 01:05:23.866
Seize her.

641
01:05:35.581 --> 01:05:36.775
Alice.

642
01:05:38.017 --> 01:05:40.315
Of course. Why didn't I see it?

643
01:05:40.352 --> 01:05:46.052
Well. it has been a long time.
and you were such a little tyke then.

644
01:05:47.092 --> 01:05:50.493
- Give me the sword.
- Stay back.

645
01:05:50.529 --> 01:05:52.656
The Queen will be so pleased.

646
01:05:52.698 --> 01:05:56.498
She will take great pleasure
in taking off your head.

647
01:06:17.156 --> 01:06:20.853
- Oh. Alice!
- Bayard! To Marmoreal.

648
01:06:29.234 --> 01:06:32.362
Majesty. Alice has escaped

649
01:06:36.408 --> 01:06:39.070
on the Bandersnatch.

650
01:06:41.513 --> 01:06:44.209
with the Vorpal sword.

651
01:06:47.353 --> 01:06:49.617
How could you let this happen?

652
01:06:50.489 --> 01:06:56.189
I may have underestimated her.
but we have her conspirators.

653
01:06:56.595 --> 01:07:00.725
the Hatter and a dormouse.

654
01:07:01.433 --> 01:07:02.764
Off with their heads!

655
01:07:21.920 --> 01:07:23.751
Welcome to Marmoreal.

656
01:07:23.789 --> 01:07:25.950
I believe this belongs to you.

657
01:07:33.399 --> 01:07:34.559
Mmm.

658
01:07:39.471 --> 01:07:41.939
The Vorpal sword is home again.

659
01:07:44.376 --> 01:07:46.310
The armor is complete.

660
01:07:49.648 --> 01:07:52.776
Now all we need is a champion.

661
01:07:54.586 --> 01:07:57.077
You're a little taller
than I thought you'd be.

662
01:07:57.122 --> 01:07:59.488
Blame it on too much upelkuchen.

663
01:07:59.558 --> 01:08:00.820
Oh.

664
01:08:00.859 --> 01:08:02.349
Come with me.

665
01:08:07.900 --> 01:08:09.458
Is the March Hare here?

666
01:08:09.501 --> 01:08:12.993
You're late
for your soup. you wee besom.

667
01:08:13.072 --> 01:08:14.801
- You're late for your soup.
- Could use some salt.

668
01:08:14.840 --> 01:08:17.001
Come here. you!

669
01:08:17.676 --> 01:08:19.837
Give me that here.
Choppy. chop. chop. chop.

670
01:08:19.912 --> 01:08:21.641
Leek and potato. Yes. That would be...

671
01:08:23.182 --> 01:08:26.640
Pishsalver. Let me think.

672
01:08:27.252 --> 01:08:29.777
A pinch of worm fat.

673
01:08:31.623 --> 01:08:33.648
urine of the horsefly.

674
01:08:35.694 --> 01:08:37.389
buttered fingers.

675
01:08:42.367 --> 01:08:47.737
My sister preferred to study
Dominion Over Living Things.

676
01:08:49.942 --> 01:08:52.570
Tell me. how does she seem to you?

677
01:08:52.644 --> 01:08:54.339
Perfectly horrid.

678
01:08:55.981 --> 01:09:00.008
- And her head?
- Bulbous.

679
01:09:01.053 --> 01:09:04.181
I think she may have
some kind of growth in there.

680
01:09:04.223 --> 01:09:06.555
something pressing on her brain.

681
01:09:06.592 --> 01:09:12.030
Three coins from a dead man's pocket.
two teaspoons of wishful thinking.

682
01:09:12.531 --> 01:09:15.932
You can't imagine the things
that go on in that place.

683
01:09:16.001 --> 01:09:17.366
Oh. yes. I can.

684
01:09:18.337 --> 01:09:23.274
But when a champion steps forth
to slay the Jabberwocky.

685
01:09:23.342 --> 01:09:25.742
the people will rise against her.

686
01:09:28.680 --> 01:09:30.375
That should do it.

687
01:09:33.819 --> 01:09:34.911
Blow.

688
01:09:49.368 --> 01:09:51.962
- Feel better?
- Much. thank you.

689
01:09:52.037 --> 01:09:54.403
There's someone here
who would like to speak with you.

690
01:10:15.127 --> 01:10:17.561
- Absolem?
- Who are you?

691
01:10:22.134 --> 01:10:26.571
I thought we'd settled this.
I'm Alice. but not that one.

692
01:10:27.072 --> 01:10:30.064
- How do you know?
- You said so yourself.

693
01:10:30.108 --> 01:10:32.474
I said you were not hardly Alice.

694
01:10:32.544 --> 01:10:34.102
but you're much more her now.

695
01:10:34.146 --> 01:10:37.081
In fact. you're almost Alice.

696
01:10:37.716 --> 01:10:39.115
Even so.

697
01:10:39.151 --> 01:10:42.086
I couldn't slay the Jabberwocky
if my life depended on it.

698
01:10:42.387 --> 01:10:43.649
It will.

699
01:10:44.756 --> 01:10:47.384
So I suggest
you keep the Vorpal sword on hand

700
01:10:47.459 --> 01:10:50.189
when the Frabjous Day arrives.

701
01:10:50.262 --> 01:10:51.957
You seem so real.

702
01:10:52.965 --> 01:10:55.957
Sometimes I forget
that this is all a dream.

703
01:10:58.637 --> 01:11:00.628
Will you stop doing that?

704
01:11:19.858 --> 01:11:22.326
I've always admired that hat.

705
01:11:23.695 --> 01:11:25.458
Hello. Chess.

706
01:11:25.497 --> 01:11:28.227
Since you won't be needing it
anymore.

707
01:11:29.635 --> 01:11:32.502
would you consider
bequeathing it to me?

708
01:11:32.537 --> 01:11:34.027
How dare you?

709
01:11:34.473 --> 01:11:38.409
It is a formal execution.
I would like to look my best. you know.

710
01:11:38.677 --> 01:11:40.838
It is a pity about all this.

711
01:11:40.879 --> 01:11:44.076
I was looking forward
to seeing you Futterwacken.

712
01:11:44.816 --> 01:11:47.148
I was rather good at it. was I not?

713
01:11:47.185 --> 01:11:50.177
I really do love that hat.

714
01:11:51.657 --> 01:11:54.524
I would wear it
to all the finest occasions.

715
01:12:02.234 --> 01:12:04.395
I love a morning execution. don't you?

716
01:12:04.469 --> 01:12:07.063
- Yes. Your Majesty.
- Yes. Your Majesty.

717
01:12:49.681 --> 01:12:52.479
- I'd like to keep it on.
- Suit yourself.

718
01:12:53.185 --> 01:12:55.653
As long as I can get at your neck.

719
01:12:57.589 --> 01:12:59.420
I'm right behind you.

720
01:13:00.158 --> 01:13:01.318
Off with his head!

721
01:13:01.526 --> 01:13:03.050
I can't watch.

722
01:13:36.595 --> 01:13:38.495
Good morning. everyone.

723
01:13:38.930 --> 01:13:41.421
Chess. you dog.

724
01:13:43.835 --> 01:13:44.961
Madam.

725
01:13:45.003 --> 01:13:46.664
you are being heinously bamboozled

726
01:13:46.738 --> 01:13:50.367
by these lickspittle toadies
you surround yourselves with.

727
01:13:54.846 --> 01:13:55.938
What is that?

728
01:13:55.981 --> 01:13:58.279
I'm not the only one. Majesty. Look!

729
01:13:58.316 --> 01:14:00.307
A counterfeit nose.
You should be ashamed.

730
01:14:00.352 --> 01:14:03.913
Me? What about that big belly
you're so proud of?

731
01:14:08.827 --> 01:14:13.389
Liars! Cheats! Falsifiers!

732
01:14:13.832 --> 01:14:15.663
Off with their heads!

733
01:14:20.505 --> 01:14:23.736
The abused and enslaved
in the Red Queen's court.

734
01:14:24.276 --> 01:14:26.801
all of you stand up and fight!

735
01:14:27.446 --> 01:14:30.040
Rise up against the bloody Red Queen.

736
01:14:32.884 --> 01:14:35.284
<i>- Downal wyth Bluddy Behg Hid!
- Downal wyth Bluddy Behg Hid!</i>

737
01:14:42.360 --> 01:14:43.918
Release the Jubjub Bird!

738
01:15:08.553 --> 01:15:10.316
You're right. Stayne.

739
01:15:10.856 --> 01:15:13.654
it is far better to be feared than loved.

740
01:15:17.762 --> 01:15:19.696
Come. boys. Quickly! Come on!

741
01:15:23.535 --> 01:15:24.695
Hatter!

742
01:15:24.736 --> 01:15:27.569
Come on. Mally. quickly.
Come on. Come on.

743
01:15:29.374 --> 01:15:34.209
Prepare the Jabberwocky for battle.
We're going to visit my little sister.

744
01:15:44.589 --> 01:15:47.217
I had hoped
to have a champion by now.

745
01:15:49.761 --> 01:15:52.127
Why don't you slay
the Jabberwocky yourself?

746
01:15:52.197 --> 01:15:53.892
You must have the power.

747
01:15:53.932 --> 01:15:57.163
It is against my vows
to harm any living creature.

748
01:16:06.478 --> 01:16:08.070
We have company.

749
01:16:17.923 --> 01:16:19.686
Have a look. Bayard.

750
01:16:22.627 --> 01:16:23.958
Bielle.

751
01:16:32.270 --> 01:16:34.101
I'm so happy to see you.
I thought they were going to...

752
01:16:34.139 --> 01:16:37.802
So did I. But they didn't.
and now here I am. still in one piece.

753
01:16:37.842 --> 01:16:40.834
And I'm rather glad about that
now that I'm seeing you again.

754
01:16:40.912 --> 01:16:42.641
I would have regretted
not seeing you again.

755
01:16:42.681 --> 01:16:45.650
especially now that you're you.
and the proper size.

756
01:16:45.817 --> 01:16:48.718
And it's a good size. It's a great size.
It's a right proper Alice size!

757
01:16:48.787 --> 01:16:52.655
- Hatter.
- Size. Fez. I'm fine.

758
01:16:52.724 --> 01:16:54.385
Where's your hat?

759
01:16:57.696 --> 01:16:58.993
Mmm.

760
01:17:00.165 --> 01:17:02.793
- Cheshire.
- How's the arm. love?

761
01:17:03.802 --> 01:17:04.996
All healed.

762
01:17:05.036 --> 01:17:07.698
Goodbye. sweet hat.

763
01:17:27.359 --> 01:17:31.386
Have you any idea
why a raven is like a writing desk?

764
01:17:34.332 --> 01:17:36.323
Let me think about it.

765
01:17:37.669 --> 01:17:40.263
You know what tomorrow is. don't you?

766
01:17:43.541 --> 01:17:46.032
Frabjous Day. How could I forget?

767
01:17:47.245 --> 01:17:48.940
Wish I'd wake up.

768
01:17:50.649 --> 01:17:54.278
- Still believe this is a dream. do you?
- Of course.

769
01:17:55.587 --> 01:17:58.215
This has all come from my own mind.

770
01:18:00.692 --> 01:18:04.128
Which would mean that I'm not real.

771
01:18:07.832 --> 01:18:12.360
Afraid so.
You're just a figment of my imagination.

772
01:18:13.705 --> 01:18:16.401
I would dream up someone
who's half-mad.

773
01:18:17.175 --> 01:18:20.872
Yes. yes. But you would have to be
half-mad to dream me up.

774
01:18:24.516 --> 01:18:26.177
I must be. then.

775
01:18:31.089 --> 01:18:33.353
I'll miss you when I wake up.

776
01:18:48.540 --> 01:18:52.476
Who will step forth to be champion
for the White Queen?

777
01:18:53.912 --> 01:18:55.743
That would be I.

778
01:18:57.382 --> 01:19:02.285
You have very poor evaporating skills.
I should be the one.

779
01:19:02.420 --> 01:19:03.512
I'll do it.

780
01:19:03.955 --> 01:19:08.119
- No. me.
- No. me.

781
01:19:25.210 --> 01:19:27.405
No other slayer. nohow.

782
01:19:27.479 --> 01:19:29.913
If it ain't Alice. it ain't dead.

783
01:19:35.920 --> 01:19:40.550
Alice. you cannot live your life
to please others.

784
01:19:41.159 --> 01:19:43.423
The choice must be yours.

785
01:19:44.229 --> 01:19:47.357
because when you step out
to face that creature.

786
01:19:48.900 --> 01:19:50.925
you will step out alone.

787
01:20:25.003 --> 01:20:28.166
Nothing was ever accomplished
with tears.

788
01:20:30.141 --> 01:20:31.472
Absolem?

789
01:20:32.777 --> 01:20:34.642
Why are you upside down?

790
01:20:34.679 --> 01:20:37.204
I've come to the end of this life.

791
01:20:38.082 --> 01:20:41.677
- You're going to die?
- Transform.

792
01:20:41.719 --> 01:20:45.280
Don't go. I need your help.
I don't know what to do.

793
01:20:46.157 --> 01:20:49.251
I can't help you if you don't even know
who you are. stupid girl.

794
01:20:49.327 --> 01:20:50.885
I'm not stupid.

795
01:20:51.663 --> 01:20:54.188
My name is Alice. I live in London.

796
01:20:54.232 --> 01:20:57.224
I have a mother named Helen
and a sister named Margaret.

797
01:20:57.268 --> 01:20:59.429
My father was Charles Kingsleigh.

798
01:20:59.504 --> 01:21:01.563
He had a vision that stretched
halfway around the world.

799
01:21:01.606 --> 01:21:03.631
and nothing ever stopped him.

800
01:21:03.708 --> 01:21:06.506
I'm his daughter. I'm Alice Kingsleigh.

801
01:21:07.011 --> 01:21:10.276
Alice. at last.

802
01:21:10.949 --> 01:21:12.974
You were just as dim-witted
the first time you were here.

803
01:21:13.051 --> 01:21:15.815
You called it "Wonderland." as I recall.

804
01:21:18.690 --> 01:21:20.123
Wonderland.

805
01:21:21.426 --> 01:21:24.953
- What do you call yourself?
- Alice.

806
01:21:25.029 --> 01:21:26.724
The Alice?

807
01:21:26.764 --> 01:21:29.961
Then I'll take you to the Hare
and the Hatter. but that's the end of it.

808
01:21:30.034 --> 01:21:32.059
<i>McTWISP: She's the right one.
I'm certain of it.</i>

809
01:21:32.103 --> 01:21:34.571
Ah. Thackery. not at the table. please.

810
01:21:34.606 --> 01:21:35.800
Have some tea.

811
01:21:35.874 --> 01:21:38.399
<i>You're not Absolem.
I'm Absolem. stupid girl.</i>

812
01:21:39.944 --> 01:21:42.071
- What is this?
- I'm Tweedledee. he's Tweedledum.

813
01:21:42.113 --> 01:21:44.604
Contrariwise. I'm Tweedledum.
he's Tweedledee.

814
01:21:44.649 --> 01:21:46.947
<i>You'd think she would
remember all this from the first time.</i>

815
01:21:46.985 --> 01:21:48.919
<i>Curiouser and curiouser.</i>

816
01:21:49.621 --> 01:21:52.749
It wasn't a dream at all.
it was a memory.

817
01:21:53.658 --> 01:21:57.617
This place is real.
and so are you and so is the Hatter.

818
01:21:57.896 --> 01:22:00.330
And the Jabberwocky.

819
01:22:01.232 --> 01:22:04.633
Remember. the Vorpal sword
knows what it wants.

820
01:22:04.669 --> 01:22:07.502
All you have to do is hold on to it.

821
01:22:10.008 --> 01:22:15.537
Fairfarren. Alice.
Perhaps I will see you in another life.

822
01:24:15.533 --> 01:24:20.061
- Hello. Iracebeth.
- Hello. Mirana.

823
01:24:23.374 --> 01:24:28.437
On this. the Frabjous Day.
the Queens Red and White

824
01:24:28.479 --> 01:24:33.178
shall send forth their champions
to do battle on their behalf.

825
01:24:34.385 --> 01:24:37.650
Oh. Racie. We don't have to fight.

826
01:24:40.124 --> 01:24:42.183
I know what you're doing.

827
01:24:42.460 --> 01:24:45.623
You think you can blink
those pretty little eyes

828
01:24:45.663 --> 01:24:48.689
and I'll melt.
just like Mummy and Daddy did.

829
01:24:50.768 --> 01:24:51.996
Please.

830
01:24:53.504 --> 01:24:58.532
No! It is my crown! I am the eldest!

831
01:24:59.243 --> 01:25:00.733
Jabberwocky!

832
01:25:48.226 --> 01:25:50.023
This is impossible.

833
01:25:50.895 --> 01:25:52.920
Only if you believe it is.

834
01:25:58.803 --> 01:26:03.831
Sometimes I believe as many as six
impossible things before breakfast.

835
01:26:04.809 --> 01:26:06.970
That is an excellent practice.

836
01:26:09.280 --> 01:26:11.908
However. just at the moment.

837
01:26:13.484 --> 01:26:16.351
you really might want
to focus on the Jabberwocky.

838
01:26:22.593 --> 01:26:24.891
Where's your champion. Sister?

839
01:26:26.330 --> 01:26:27.524
Here.

840
01:26:29.834 --> 01:26:31.199
Hello. Um.

841
01:26:45.283 --> 01:26:48.411
Six impossible things.
Count them. Alice.

842
01:26:53.024 --> 01:26:56.118
One. there's a potion
that can make you shrink.

843
01:26:59.697 --> 01:27:02.427
Two. and a cake
that can make you grow.

844
01:27:02.967 --> 01:27:09.463
So. my old foe.
we meet on the battlefield once again.

845
01:27:10.708 --> 01:27:12.107
We've never met.

846
01:27:12.143 --> 01:27:14.543
Not you. insignificant bearer.

847
01:27:15.413 --> 01:27:19.941
My ancient enemy. the Vorpal one.

848
01:27:21.252 --> 01:27:23.152
That's enough chatter.

849
01:27:30.061 --> 01:27:32.655
Three. animals can talk.

850
01:27:38.402 --> 01:27:39.869
Four. Alice.

851
01:27:42.273 --> 01:27:44.138
cats can disappear.

852
01:27:46.644 --> 01:27:47.804
Five.

853
01:27:50.881 --> 01:27:53.372
there's a place called Wonderland.

854
01:27:54.218 --> 01:27:55.378
Six.

855
01:27:56.153 --> 01:27:58.121
I can slay the Jabberwocky.

856
01:28:23.648 --> 01:28:26.583
The Hatter's interfering!
Off with his head!

857
01:30:53.364 --> 01:30:55.161
Off with your head!

858
01:31:27.798 --> 01:31:29.823
Kill her!

859
01:31:29.867 --> 01:31:32.529
We follow you no more.
Bloody Big Head.

860
01:31:32.670 --> 01:31:35.230
How dare you? Off with his head!

861
01:32:17.248 --> 01:32:22.584
Iracebeth of Crims. your crimes
against Underland are worthy of death.

862
01:32:24.588 --> 01:32:28.149
However. that is against my vows.

863
01:32:29.460 --> 01:32:31.894
therefore. you are banished
to the Outlands.

864
01:32:32.363 --> 01:32:36.322
No one is to show you any kindness.
or ever speak a word to you.

865
01:32:39.370 --> 01:32:42.203
You will not have a friend in the world.

866
01:32:43.841 --> 01:32:48.278
Majesty. I hope you bear me no ill will.

867
01:32:51.916 --> 01:32:54.544
Only this one. Ilosovic Stayne.

868
01:32:54.618 --> 01:32:56.609
you are to join Iracebeth in banishment

869
01:32:56.654 --> 01:32:59.452
from this day
until the end of Underland.

870
01:33:02.326 --> 01:33:04.521
At least we have each other.

871
01:33:17.608 --> 01:33:22.011
Majesty. please! Kill me! Please!

872
01:33:22.713 --> 01:33:25.011
But I do not owe you a kindness.

873
01:33:25.049 --> 01:33:28.018
- Take off my head!
- He tried to kill me.

874
01:33:28.052 --> 01:33:31.317
- Majesty! Please! Please!
- He tried to kill me.

875
01:33:31.355 --> 01:33:33.323
- I offer you my head!
- He tried to kill me!

876
01:33:33.357 --> 01:33:36.656
Oh. the Frabjous Day! Callou! Callay!

877
01:33:43.200 --> 01:33:46.328
- What is he doing?
- Futterwacken.

878
01:34:32.950 --> 01:34:37.751
Blood of the Jabberwocky.
You have our everlasting gratitude.

879
01:34:38.122 --> 01:34:40.682
And for your efforts on our behalf...

880
01:34:44.928 --> 01:34:48.295
- Will this take me home?
- If that is what you choose.

881
01:35:14.758 --> 01:35:16.350
You could stay.

882
01:35:19.697 --> 01:35:23.633
What an idea.
A crazy. mad. wonderful idea.

883
01:35:29.606 --> 01:35:31.073
But I can't.

884
01:35:32.476 --> 01:35:36.537
There are questions I have to answer.
things I have to do.

885
01:35:45.155 --> 01:35:47.555
Be back again before you know it.

886
01:35:49.193 --> 01:35:51.058
You won't remember me.

887
01:35:51.829 --> 01:35:54.559
Of course I will. How could I forget?

888
01:35:59.369 --> 01:36:03.328
Hatter. why is a raven
like a writing desk?

889
01:36:05.642 --> 01:36:07.906
I haven't the slightest idea.

890
01:36:13.083 --> 01:36:14.846
Fairfarren. Alice.

891
01:37:01.965 --> 01:37:04.991
She left me standing there
without an answer.

892
01:37:05.068 --> 01:37:07.229
A case of nerves. no doubt.

893
01:37:10.207 --> 01:37:12.607
- Alice.
- Good Lord.

894
01:37:13.443 --> 01:37:15.741
- Are you all right?
- What happened to you?

895
01:37:15.779 --> 01:37:18.839
I fell down a hole and hit my head.

896
01:37:19.116 --> 01:37:23.610
I'm sorry. Hamish. I can't marry you.
You're not the right man for me.

897
01:37:25.122 --> 01:37:28.114
And there's that trouble
with your digestion.

898
01:37:29.126 --> 01:37:33.654
I love you. Margaret. but this is my life.
I'll decide what to do with it.

899
01:37:37.034 --> 01:37:40.526
You're lucky to have my sister
for your wife. Lowell.

900
01:37:40.604 --> 01:37:44.335
and you be good to her.
I'll be watching very closely.

901
01:37:46.844 --> 01:37:49.335
There is no prince. Aunt Imogene.

902
01:37:49.413 --> 01:37:52.610
You need to talk to someone
about these delusions.

903
01:37:54.985 --> 01:37:58.148
I happen to love rabbits.
especially white ones.

904
01:38:01.091 --> 01:38:02.353
Don't worry. Mother.

905
01:38:02.426 --> 01:38:05.395
I'll find something useful
to do with my life.

906
01:38:07.497 --> 01:38:10.989
You two remind me of some funny boys
I met in a dream.

907
01:38:13.270 --> 01:38:16.205
- You've left me out.
- No. I haven't. sir.

908
01:38:17.040 --> 01:38:19.702
You and I have business to discuss.

909
01:38:19.776 --> 01:38:21.971
Shall we speak in the study?

910
01:38:28.685 --> 01:38:30.880
Oh. And one more thing.

911
01:38:39.062 --> 01:38:43.931
My father told me he planned to expand
his trade route to Sumatra and Borneo.

912
01:38:44.001 --> 01:38:46.561
but I don't think
he was looking far enough.

913
01:38:46.603 --> 01:38:48.901
Why not go all the way to China?

914
01:38:49.706 --> 01:38:54.040
It's vast. the culture is rich.
and we have a foothold in Hong Kong.

915
01:38:54.845 --> 01:38:58.406
To be the first to trade with China.
can you imagine it?

916
01:39:00.384 --> 01:39:02.045
You know. if anybody else
had said that to me.

917
01:39:02.085 --> 01:39:05.020
I'd say. "You've lost your senses".

918
01:39:05.222 --> 01:39:07.417
But I've seen that look before.

919
01:39:07.557 --> 01:39:12.051
Well. as you're not going to be
my daughter-in-law.

920
01:39:12.095 --> 01:39:16.054
perhaps you'd consider becoming
an apprentice with the company.

921
01:39:55.939 --> 01:39:57.600
Hello. Absolem.

922
01:40:13.390 --> 01:40:16.826
<i>Tripping out. spinning around</i>

923
01:40:16.893 --> 01:40:21.853
<i>I'm underground
I fell down</i>

924
01:40:23.000 --> 01:40:26.128
<i>Yeah. I fell down</i>

925
01:40:29.039 --> 01:40:33.032
<i>I'm freaking out
Where am I now?</i>

926
01:40:33.110 --> 01:40:39.674
<i>Upside down and I can't stop it now</i>

927
01:40:40.150 --> 01:40:44.712
<i>Can't stop me now</i>

928
01:40:49.459 --> 01:40:56.058
<i>I. I'll get by</i>

929
01:40:57.534 --> 01:41:04.269
<i>I. I'll survive</i>

930
01:41:05.842 --> 01:41:09.801
<i>When the world's crashing down
When I fall and hit the ground</i>

931
01:41:09.846 --> 01:41:13.577
<i>I will turn myself around
Don't you try to stop me</i>

932
01:41:13.650 --> 01:41:20.351
<i>I. I won't cry</i>

933
01:41:23.493 --> 01:41:30.524
<i>I found myself in Wonderland</i>

934
01:41:31.768 --> 01:41:38.571
<i>Get back on my feet. the ground</i>

935
01:41:40.577 --> 01:41:44.377
<i>Is this real?</i>

936
01:41:44.414 --> 01:41:47.611
<i>Is it pretend?</i>

937
01:41:47.684 --> 01:41:54.590
<i>I'll take a stand until the end</i>

938
01:41:58.028 --> 01:42:04.627
<i>I. I'll get by</i>

939
01:42:06.103 --> 01:42:12.838
<i>I. I'll survive</i>

940
01:42:14.344 --> 01:42:18.440
<i>When the world's crashing down
When I fall and hit the ground</i>

941
01:42:18.515 --> 01:42:22.212
<i>I will turn myself around
Don't you try to stop me</i>

942
01:42:22.252 --> 01:42:28.953
<i>I. I won't cry</i>

943
01:43:11.935 --> 01:43:16.770
<i>Oh. Alice. dear. where have you been?</i>

944
01:43:19.809 --> 01:43:24.576
<i>So near. so far. so in between</i>

945
01:43:27.884 --> 01:43:32.344
<i>What have you heard?
What have you seen?</i>

946
01:43:32.389 --> 01:43:37.190
<i>Alice. Alice. please. Alice</i>

947
01:43:44.134 --> 01:43:48.833
<i>Oh. tell us. are you big or small?</i>

948
01:43:51.908 --> 01:43:56.436
<i>To try this one or try them all</i>

949
01:43:59.816 --> 01:44:04.412
<i>It's such a long. long way to fall</i>

950
01:44:04.454 --> 01:44:09.187
<i>Alice. Alice. oh. Alice</i>

951
01:44:16.399 --> 01:44:18.264
<i>How can you know this way. not that?</i>

952
01:44:18.301 --> 01:44:20.292
<i>You choose the door
You choose the path</i>

953
01:44:20.337 --> 01:44:22.305
<i>Perhaps you should be coming back</i>

954
01:44:22.339 --> 01:44:24.136
<i>Another day. another day</i>

955
01:44:24.174 --> 01:44:26.267
<i>And nothing is quite what it seems</i>

956
01:44:26.309 --> 01:44:28.106
<i>You're dreaming
Are you dreaming?</i>

957
01:44:28.144 --> 01:44:29.475
<i>Oh. Alice</i>

958
01:44:36.987 --> 01:44:41.014
<i>Oh. Alice</i>

959
01:44:44.527 --> 01:44:48.224
<i>Oh!</i>

960
01:45:16.092 --> 01:45:21.086
<i>Oh. how will you find your way?</i>

961
01:45:24.000 --> 01:45:29.097
<i>Oh. how will you find your way?</i>

962
01:45:36.479 --> 01:45:40.438
<i>No time for tears today
No time for tears today</i>

963
01:45:44.487 --> 01:45:48.514
<i>No time for tears today
No time for tears today</i>

964
01:46:04.240 --> 01:46:06.265
<i>So many doors. how did you choose?</i>

965
01:46:06.309 --> 01:46:08.209
<i>So much to gain. so much to lose</i>

966
01:46:08.244 --> 01:46:10.075
<i>So many things got in your way</i>

967
01:46:10.113 --> 01:46:12.172
<i>No time today. no time today</i>

968
01:46:12.215 --> 01:46:14.183
<i>Be careful not to lose your head</i>

969
01:46:14.217 --> 01:46:16.481
<i>Remember what the dormouse said</i>

970
01:46:16.519 --> 01:46:17.850
<i>Alice!</i>

971
01:46:28.064 --> 01:46:32.524
<i>Did someone pull you by the hand?</i>

972
01:46:35.939 --> 01:46:40.501
<i>How many miles to Wonderland?</i>

973
01:46:44.080 --> 01:46:48.517
<i>Please tell us so we'll understand</i>

974
01:46:48.551 --> 01:46:53.284
<i>Alice. Alice. oh. Alice</i>

975
01:47:04.067 --> 01:47:09.027
<i>Oh. how will you find your way?</i>

